John G. Ullman & Associates, Inc.


                  John G. Ullman & Associates (JGUA) manages balanced portfolios that include cash, bonds, some mutual funds and stock in individual companies. Asset allocated is mutually determined by the firm and the client. Portfolios can consist of one or more of several types of accounts established in the client's name. JGUA's investment approach sets price targets for buys and sells and sticks to those targets, removing emotion and enthusiasm from the investment process and adjusting portfolios based on strategic decision-making. The firm selects individual securities based on fundamental and technical analysis. They purchase and sell securities in large blocks, allocating shares to individual portfolios based on the client's risk tolerance and diversification objectives.                




President

                                    1972 - 1978                


Corning, Inc.


                  Corning Incorporated is the world leader in specialty glass and ceramics. Drawing on more than 160 years of materials science and process engineering knowledge, Corning creates and makes keystone components that enable high-technology systems for consumer electronics, mobile emissions control, telecommunications, and life sciences. We also serve customers in specialty materials industries, including Ophthalmics.

 

Corning’s operations in India are represented by Corning Technologies India Private Limited. Through our office in Gurgaon, we offer our customers world class products and service which includes access to our vast global technical resources, applications engineering support, after sales support, and increasingly, locally stocked products                




